body:
There are already several threads but I was hoping that maybe if we get some more threads going on this a Riot member would be bound to respond to one of them. Per-Side Offset is currently operating as Fixed Offset, showing no difference than it. For many players (including myself) it makes it difficult to play because not everybody plays with their camera unlocked. I personally play with Per-Side Offset and unlock the camera when necessary. With this bug it makes it difficult to play and I honestly may not be playing until this is addressed and fixed. I can&#039;t screen shot it at the moment but there really isn&#039;t anything to show you, just that Per-Side is also Fixed at the moment, showing no difference. Thank you in advance.

TheBlightcaller

{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-thumbs}}

replies.body:
This is literally all I (and the rest of us) wanted. I appreciate you acknowledging this issue. It will put a lot of us at rest. I didn't think you worked on these bugs and whatnot, I know there is nearly a department for everything, but I figured that perhaps you or the others were capable of forwarding this message to that department. Thank you again for popping in.

Edit: As in one of your other responses, I know that that it's the weekend now and most others are off but the reason why myself and the others were upset was because this was being posted around the area for 48 hours. Now, this _is not_ your fault. I'm not saying that this is your doing, please don't think that. Like I said above, we just wanted a thumbs up or something saying "Yo dude, we're acknowledging this issue and we'll pass it on!" Thankfully you were a little free and had a moment to respond despite this not being your expertise, which I again appreciate. I like you in particular because I've gotten some great feedback from you before with another issue. Thank you again for your time. I hope you enjoy your weekend, Katey. 

{{sticker:slayer-pantheon-thumbs}}
